 exclusion of possible kinematic contaminants. Resulting $\\Delta V$ vs.\n$s$ and $\\Delta V$ vs. $m_{B}$ scalings accurately tracing Newtonian\nexpectations for the high acceleration regime, but consistent with the distance\nand mass velocity scalings observed in spiral galaxies in the low acceleration\none, are obtained.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 Apr 2023 18:00:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-18"}
